Phishing is a trick where attackers pretend to be trustworthy people or websites to steal your personal info like passwords or credit card numbers. They might send fake emails or messages that look real, asking you to click links or enter details. These fake requests can lead to stealing your identity or money. Recognizing phishing involves checking for suspicious links, unexpected requests, or poor spelling. Searching terms like “phishing scams,” “social engineering,” or “email spoofing” can help you learn more. Being careful with messages and verifying sources protects your private data and keeps your communications safe.
